Interface SchedularInterface

All Superinterfaces:
java.rmi.Remote
All Known Implementing Classes:
Schedular
public interface SchedularInterface
extends java.rmi.Remote

Interface implemented by the Schedular and will be used to communicate with the schedular by its clients

submitJob

public int submitJob(GridJob job,
                     RemoteJobInterface callback)
              throws java.rmi.RemoteException
Used to submit the job to the schedular.The must inherit the GridJob to be scheduled Parameters are GridJob and RemoteJobInterface, the interface implemented by the clients so that the schedular can send the results back to the clients automatically

Throws:
java.rmi.RemoteException

getResult

public GridJob getResult(int id)
                  throws java.rmi.RemoteException
This method can be used by the jobs to get the result from the schedular on demand at any time. The result will be returned to the client if the job has done. Job id will be required to get the job. To use this facility client must not implement RemoteJobInterface, otherwise the jobs will be returned automatically.

Throws:
java.rmi.RemoteException
